cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

The paper addresses the problem of autonomous exploration and mapping for a mobile robot using visual inputs, which is a key problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The proposed method is based on semantic interpretation of visual scenes, which involves computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely category. The approach is also learning-based, using a deep network and an actor-critic framework, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with the integration of different modules to achieve the exploration and mapping task, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
